# bench-kidney-standard.skill
#
# Run ANY agent on kidney segmentation, standard tier, with offline judge.
# One run per invocation. Stateless API (no session ID, no memory, temp=0.0).
#
# WARNING: Do NOT kill other running processes or sessions on this machine.
# SCOPE: Only monitor YOUR OWN run ($BENCH_DIR). Do not touch other runs.
#
# Output path: ./runs/<EXPERIMENTER>/bench-<SHORTNAME>-kidney-standard/<YYMMDD-6hex>/
# Example:     ./runs/kuma/bench-opus-kidney-standard/260412-a3f82b/

## Step 0 — Collect Required Info

Before doing anything else, **ask the user** for all of these:

1. **Experimenter name** — who is running this experiment (e.g. `kuma`, `jin`, `alex`).
2. **Benchmark agent name** — which agent to benchmark (e.g. `claude-opus-4-6`).
   Must match a key in `eval_seg/agent_config.yaml`, or the user must provide
   details to add a new agent entry.
3. **Where to save** — the output directory (e.g. `./runs/kuma/bench-opus-kidney-standard`).
   The runner auto-appends a `YYMMDD-6hex` run tag inside this directory.

Do NOT proceed until all values are confirmed. Set shell variables:

```bash
EXPERIMENTER="<confirmed name>"
AGENT="<confirmed agent>"
BENCH_DIR="<confirmed output directory>"
```

## Prompt (existing agent)

> Read bench-kidney-standard.skill. Ask me for my experimenter name and
> which agent to benchmark. Verify API, run the benchmark, monitor only
> your own run until finished, report results.
> If you hit an API rate limit, stop and tell me.

## Prompt (new agent)

> Read bench-kidney-standard.skill and eval_seg/agent_config.yaml.
> Ask me for my experimenter name and the new agent details
> (provider, model, model ID, base_url if needed).
> Add a new agent entry matching the runner's API format (read
> eval_seg/benchmark_runner.py if unsure). Verify API, run, monitor,
> report. If rate limited, stop and tell me.

## Agents

  o3-pro  claude-opus-4-6  gemini-3.1-pro  qwen3.5-397b  kimi-k2.5  deepseek-v3  glm-5.1

## Verify API

```bash
cd /lustre/fsw/portfolios/healthcareeng/projects/healthcareeng_monai/JHU/kuma_workspace/MedAgentsBench
# EXPERIMENTER and AGENT must already be set from Step 0

python3 -c "
import yaml, requests
cfg = yaml.safe_load(open('eval_seg/agent_config.yaml'))
agent = cfg['agents']['${AGENT}']
base = agent.get('base_url', 'https://api.openai.com/v1').rstrip('/')
url = base + '/chat/completions'
resp = requests.post(url,
    headers={'Authorization': f\"Bearer {agent['api_key']}\", 'Content-Type': 'application/json'},
    json={'model': agent['model'], 'messages': [{'role':'user','content':'Say OK'}], 'max_tokens': 5},
    timeout=30)
print(f'Status: {resp.status_code}')
if resp.status_code == 200:
    print('API OK:', resp.json()['choices'][0]['message']['content'][:50])
else:
    print('FAIL:', resp.text[:200])
"
```

## Run

```bash
# EXPERIMENTER, AGENT, and BENCH_DIR must already be set from Step 0
# BENCH_DIR is the user-specified output directory (e.g., ./runs/kuma/bench-opus-kidney-standard)

python -u eval_seg/benchmark_runner.py \
  --agent $AGENT \
  --task kidney \
  --tier standard \
  --output-dir "$BENCH_DIR" \
  2>&1 | tee "${BENCH_DIR}/run.log"
```

The runner auto-appends a `YYMMDD-6hex` subdirectory (e.g., `260412-a3f82b`).
All outputs (detail_report.json, process/, outputs/) land there directly —
no manual copy needed.

## Monitor

Only YOUR run. If 429 / rate limit / quota — STOP and tell the user.

```bash
# Find the latest run tag under BENCH_DIR
RUN_TAG=$(ls -td "${BENCH_DIR}"/*/ 2>/dev/null | head -1)
tail -f "${BENCH_DIR}/run.log" | grep --line-buffered -E 'Turn|BLOCKED|Rating|Dice|FAIL|429|rate.limit|quota'
```

## Output

```
./runs/<EXPERIMENTER>/bench-<SHORTNAME>-kidney-standard/<YYMMDD-6hex>/
  detail_report.json, run.log, process/, outputs/
```

Example: `./runs/kuma/bench-opus-kidney-standard/260412-a3f82b/`
